  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow">Guide</p>
    <h1>Why PDF to Excel Conversions Break Table Formatting</h1>
    <p>PDFs store visual instructions, not spreadsheet logic. That is why rows, columns, and merged cells can break during conversion.</p>
    <h2>Common causes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Columns are aligned visually but not encoded as cells.</li>
      <li>Headers span multiple columns.</li>
      <li>Tables continue across page breaks.</li>
      <li>Scanned pages have no text layer.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>How to improve results</h2>
    <p>Use text-based PDFs, avoid low-quality scans, and verify totals after conversion. For scanned documents, wait for OCR support or use a dedicated OCR tool first.</p>
  </article>
